        "created_at": "2022-01-25T08:56:53.970Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi, Experts</p>\n<p>I wonder in Cloud K8S environment when I want to restart the foundationdb cluster (e.g there are 10 pods running fdb servers). How can I restart it? Just kill all pods one by one? Or there is somewhere to kick off a service restart command once to restart the whole fdb cluster? Thanks!</p>",
